---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const title = 'Research — ' + SITE_TITLE;
const description = 'Wave height forecasting and measurement in The Gulf of Trieste.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
		<script type="text/javascript" src="https://www.gstatic.com/charts/loader.js"></script>
		<script type="text/javascript">
			google.charts.load('current', {'packages':['corechart']});
			google.charts.setOnLoadCallback(drawGID);

			function drawGID() {
				var queryString = encodeURIComponent('SELECT D, H, I, J LIMIT 30');
				var query = new google.visualization.Query(
					'https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Y10YJuKOOcB7C5TDYmvRI-JfHOIbKp64K1ZK9rFwIT8/gviz/tq?gid=0&headers=1&tq=' + queryString);
				query.send(handleQueryResponse);
			}

			function handleQueryResponse(response) {
				if (response.isError()) {
					console.log('Error in query: ' + response.getMessage() + ' ' + response.getDetailedMessage());
					return;
				}
				var data = response.getDataTable();
				var wrapper = new google.visualization.ChartWrapper({
					chartType: 'ColumnChart',
					dataTable: data,
					containerId: 'chart_div',
					options: {
						legend: { position: 'top', alignment: 'start' },
						title: 'Significant Wave Height for Today - buoy Vida location',
						titleTextStyle: {
							fontSize: 20,
							bold: true
						},
						chartArea: {width: '80%', height: '50%'},
						hAxis: {direction: 1, slantedText: true, slantedTextAngle: 90},
						vAxis: {
							format: 'short',
							viewWindow: { min: 0 },
							viewWindowMode: 'explicit',
							title: 'Significant Wave Height - SWH [m]'
						},
						height: '500',
						width: '100%'
					}
				});
				wrapper.draw();
			}
		</script>
		<style>
			#chart_div {
				width: 100%;
				margin: 2rem 0;
				min-height: 300px;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Research</h1>

			<h2>Wave height in The Gulf of Trieste — forecast and measurement</h2>

			<p>
				There are 3 buoys [1] in the Gulf of Trieste operated by Slovenian Environment Agency (ARSO)
				which make wave height measurements. Buoy Vida is taking measurements from 2006 [2].
				There are multiple numerical models which predict wave climate. One of those is WAM model
				from National and Kapodistrian University of Athens [3]. Wave model predominately underestimates
				high sea waves in the Gulf of Trieste. Therefore, adjustment equation corrects WAM model data [4].
			</p>

			<p>Graph shows following data for the current day in the local time on the coordinates of buoy Vida:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>WAM numerical model wave height</li>
				<li>WAM numerical model wave height adjusted</li>
				<li>Buoy Vida wave height measurement</li>
			</ul>

			<div id="chart_div"></div>

			<p>
				Nowadays weather forecast for the next few days is quite reliable. However, reliability in unstable
				weather conditions is lower. Wave height prediction is based on weather forecast. Therefore, numerical
				models for wave forecast are even less reliable. As duration of continuous measurements with buoys is
				relatively short in the Gulf of Trieste (from 2006), wave data can be extended with results of numerical
				models. This is beneficial for calculation of design wave height.
			</p>

			<p>
				It was found out that WAM numerical model for wave forecast predominately underestimates high seas waves.
				Therefore, equation to adjust numerical wave height from typical wave directions with high seas was
				defined for the Gulf of Trieste [4].
			</p>

			<h3>References</h3>
			<ol>
				<li>
					<a href="http://rte.arso.gov.si/vode/poro%C4%8Dila%20in%20publikacije/Program%20hidrolo%C5%A1kega%20monitoringa%20povr%C5%A1inskih%20voda%202016-2020.pdf"
					   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						ARSO — Hydrological monitoring programme for surface waters 2016–2020 (PDF)
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://www.nib.si/mbp/sl/oceanografski-podatki/buoy-2/live-data-2"
					   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						NIB — Buoy Vida live data
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://forecast.uoa.gr/en/group"
					   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						National and Kapodistrian University of Athens — Forecast group
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://repozitorij.uni-lj.si/IzpisGradiva.php?id=32512"
					   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						University of Ljubljana repository — Wave height adjustment equation
					</a>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
